OL,3,CWhy the family of murdered MP Sir
OL,4,CDavid Amess deserve answers
OL,6,FThey are especially angry with James
OL,7,FCleverly, who saw himself as a friend
OL,8,Fof Sir David. They feel that if the
OL,9,FHome Office, when he was Home
OL,10,FSecretary, had said the inquest should
OL,11,Fbe re-opened, it would have been.
OL,13,FInstead the Home Office made what it
OL,14,Fdescribed as a "neutral" submission to
OL,15,Fthe coroner. Katie is concerned its
OL,16,Ftone and content may have been hostile
OL,17,Fto the statute-based inquiry she seeks.
